cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.NE 

The paper presents a new approach to multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method involves approximating interactions within a population of agents, which is a common problem in multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses the convergence of the solution, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY) and neural networks (cs.NE).
